</div></div>
</div>
</section>
</aside>
</aside><p>“I don’t,” AliKhan replied.</p>
<p>Shedd suggested that Trump was being put in a no-win situation, where if he made more aggressive efforts to avoid business from foreign sources he would face further litigation.</p>
<p>“If he then said — a little reminiscent of the travel ban —&nbsp;no foreigners can stay in any of my properties, how long before the State of Maryland would sue him for discrimination?” the judge asked. “What you want to do is make it a guessing game for him.”</p>
<p>Judge Paul Niemeyer called Messitte's handling of the case in the lower court “very peculiar.” Niemeyer noted that the district judge suggested early in the case that D.C. and Maryland might need to name the president personally as a defendant, rather than just in his official capacity as president. They then did that. Later, Messitte inquired about dismissing the president personally from the suit and the plaintiffs soon did that.</p>
<p>“It sounds like the court was doing something beyond just responding to the parties,” said Niemeyer, an appointee of President George H.W. Bush.</p>
<p>“Does that not look like the district court is somehow involved in guiding this?” Shedd asked. “It looks a little bit odd.”</p>
<p>Shedd also ridiculed Maryland’s argument that Trump’s actions were undermining the basic terms under which the state agreed to join the union in 1788.</p>
<p>“I hope that if the courts disagree with you, you’re not thinking about seceding from the union, are you?” Shedd asked.</p>
<p>“I confess, I am from the District of Columbia, so I don’t think I’d be allowed to secede,” AliKhan said.</p><aside class="story-related">
<article class="story-frag format-sm">
<figure class="thumb">
<div class="fig-graphic">
<a href="https://www.politico.com/story/2019/03/19/trump-democrat-oversight-investigation-congress-1225761" target="_top" class="js-tealium-tracking" data-tracking="mpos=inside body&amp;mid=ParentheticalModule&amp;lindex=Unknown&amp;lcol=Unknown"><img data-lazy-img="https://static.politico.com/dims4/default/acb75ca/2147483647/thumbnail/90x49%3E/quality/90/?url=https%3A%2F%2Fstatic.politico.com%2F72%2Fda%2F933085024e1787ac88706feef5b7%2F190318-trump-pelosi-gty-773.jpg" width="90" height="49" src="data:image/gif;base64,R0lGODlhAQABAAAAACH5BAEKAAEALAAAAAABAAEAAAICTAEAOw==" alt="Donald Trump and Nancy Pelosi" data-size="promo_xsmall_rectangle"></a></div>
</figure>
<div class="summary">
<header>
<p class="category">
<a href="https://www.politico.com/white-house" target="_blank" class="js-tealium-tracking" data-tracking="mpos=inside body&amp;mid=ParentheticalModule&amp;lindex=Unknown&amp;lcol=Unknown">White House</a></p>
